      • setStudentAndClient

        public void setStudentAndClient​(logic.Users Student,
                                ChatClient client,
                                logic.StudentInTest studentInTest,
                                InExamController inExamController,
                                logic.Test test)
        This function sets the student, chat client, student in test, in exam controller, and test for a given user when the test tybe is Digital
        Parameters:
        Student - An object of the class Users representing a student.
        client - The ChatClient object that represents the connection between the student and the server in the Digital exam.
        studentInTest - It is an object that represents a student's information and progress in a test. It contain attributes such as the student's answers, time remaining, and current question number.
        inExamController - It is an object of the InExamController class, which is responsible for controlling the user interface and logic during an Digital exam.
        test - The test parameter is an object of the Test class, which contains information about the test that the student is taking. This information includes the test name, duration, number of questions, and other relevant details.
